    <section id="pricing-intro" class="clearfix content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="white-bg pricing-finance-wrap clearfix">
          <div class="pricing-finance-icon">
            <img loading="lazy" 
              src="./uploads/2025/04/CityClinics-Available.png"
              alt="0 percent financing"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-finance-copy">
            <h2>0% Financing Available</h2>
            <p>Finance your transplant at 0% interest for up to 12 months.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="title-content clearfix">
          <div class="title-inner">
            <p>How our pricing works</p>
            <h3>What Is Transparent Pricing?</h3>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pricing-grid pricing-grid-2 clearfix">
          <div class="pricing-col">
            <div class="white-bg padding pricing-note pricing-note-negative">
              <h4>The Traditional Pricing Model</h4>
              <p>
                Per-graft charging can appear low at first but often creates an
                incentive to over-quote grafts and increase final costs.
              </p>
              <p>
                Many clinics price every graft individually, which can lead to
                quotes that exceed what is truly needed for natural coverage.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-col">
            <div class="white-bg padding pricing-note pricing-note-positive">
              <h4>Our Fixed Package Pricing</h4>
              <p>
                Official Hair Clinic uses fixed transplant size categories:
                small, medium, large, and mega.
              </p>
              <p>
                Your surgeon assesses donor and recipient zones, then recommends
                the right package to achieve natural density without overpaying.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
      <div class="clearfix"></div>
